	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Music from 1001 Spikes</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It is possible to use multiple expansions in a single .NSF. The only thing to be careful of is not to write to a sound register which is also FDS RAM if you are not trying to change the program data at that address too.<br /><br />There appears to be less than 255 songs so you might put it in a NSF as long as it also fits in less than 255 ROM banks.<br /><br />I am not interested in downloading rendered audio of 69 tracks, whether or not it is for pay, although perhaps a physical CD might do.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


