	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Music from 1001 Spikes</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It is possible to do a single NSF with multiple expansion audio like I have mentioned above; you only have to be aware of conflicts with FDS RAM. In case the music will not fit directly, you can choose to compress it, and to decompress the music at runtime, during the INIT routine, into RAM (which, due to FDS, you should have enough of, although you should reserve some banks to be used only for RAM in order that conflicts are not caused due to the implementation of the NSF player).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


